1. Step of Full RMAN RECOVERY ? (in case oracle s/w is missing, we need to install oracle s/w).

	=> Set ENV 
	-> RMAN target / 
	-> RMAN> startup (DB will open in nomount mode) 
	-> Restore SPFILE from '/backup_location/';  
	-> Shutdown immediate
	-> Startup (nomount)
	-> Restore controlfile from '/backup_location/';
	-> Alter database mount;
	-> Restore database;
	-> Recover database;
	-> Alter database open RESETLOGS; (Reset the log sequence number for complete recovery.)
	-> Take a fresh full backup again.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

2. Restore parameter file (spfile/pfile) from backup ?

=> Set ENV
=> Rman target / (RMAN> prompt will open even parameter file missing for recovery)
=> DB will open in 'Nomount' mode
=> restore spfile from '/u01/app/oracle/fast_recovery_area/prod/autobackup/2026_05_10/o1_mf_s_123abc_.bkp';
=> shutdown immediate
=> startup (means parameter file has now restored)
=> restore controlfile from '/u01/app/oracle/fast_recovery_area/prod/autobackup/2026_05_10/o1_mf_s_123abc_.bkp'; 
=> alter database mount (because we have now controlfile, so it will open in mount state)
=> Restore database;
=> Recover database;
=> Alter database open RESETLOGS;

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
3. Take Backup when my backup location is diffrent not the default one (FRA) ?

	=> Set ENV
	-> RMAN target /
	-> RMAN> startup (DB will open in nomount mode if control file is missing) 
	-> Restore CONTROLfile from '/u01/app/oracle/backup_location/ol_mf_123.bkp';
	-> Alter database mount;
	-> catalog start with '/new_backup_location';
	-> Restore database;
	-> Recover database;
	-> Alter database open RESETLOGS; (Reset the log sequence number for complete recovery.)
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

