8. Why use CONSISTANT=Y parammeter in logical backup ?

=> ✅ CONSISTENT=Y is used in logical backups to export data in a single consistent state by using undo information, ensuring data integrity during export.

	👉 exp system/password FULL=Y CONSISTENT=Y FILE=full.dmp LOG=full.log

	✅ Without CONSISTENT=Y:

		👉Tables are exported one by one

		👉 If users are doing INSERT/UPDATE/DELETE:

		👉 Some tables may be exported before commit

		👉 Some tables may be exported after commit

		👉 Result → inconsistent backup

	✅ With CONSISTENT=Y:

		👉 Export uses UNDO data

		👉 All tables are read from the same SCN (System Change Number)

	✅ ORA-01555: snapshot too old --- error occured without CONSISTENT=Y

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

9. What is database REFRESH Activity ?

=> ✅	 A Database Refresh is the process of copying data from a source database 
			(PROD or another environment) to a target database (TEST, DEV, or UAT). 

	-> To do this with RMAN 
	-> EXpdp / IMpdp

	Using RMAN :: 
		👉 take backup in production DB
		👉 transfer this backup in the DEV DB
		👉 restore backup in the DEV DB
		👉 Now, if DEV has more extra objects then after restore PROD backup all are gone.
		So, prevent this we use - EXPDP/IMPDP
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

