17. Scope = both, Scope = memery,  Scope = spfile - purposes ?

✅ SCOPE = MEMORY
👉 All changes happend in memory(RAM), after DB restart changes are gone
👉 USE CASE: Temporary fix, Testing purpose.
👉 SYNTAX : ALTER SYSTEM SET UNDO_RETENTION = 3600 SCOPE = MEMORY;

✅ SCOPE = SPFILE
👉 All changes happend in SPFILE, After restart changes will effect.
👉 USE CASE: Want changes effect after restart.
👉 SYNTAX : ALTER SYSTEM SET SGA_MAX_SIZE = 8G SCOPE = SPFILE;

✅ SCOPE = BOTH
👉 All changes happend in both memory & SPFILE. Instant effect not need to restart.
👉 USE CASE: Permanent changes needed.
👉 ALTER SYSTEM SET UNDO_RETENTION = 3600 SCOPE = BOTH;

