20. How to take level 0 incremental backup syntax ?
=> 
-- Level 0 incremental backup (base for incremental strategy)
BACKUP INCREMENTAL LEVEL 0 DATABASE;

-- Level 1 incremental (captures changes since Level 0)
BACKUP INCREMENTAL LEVEL 1 DATABASE;

-- Differential (default) - backs up changes since last Level 0 or 1
BACKUP INCREMENTAL LEVEL 1 DATABASE;

-- Cumulative - backs up all changes since last Level 0
BACKUP INCREMENTAL LEVEL 1 CUMULATIVE DATABASE;
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

